100783.title: little parrot Agapornis Roseicollis.aif
100783.description: Here is a beautiful sound of little parrot (Latin name: Agapornis Roseicollis) that I recorded in the Belgrade zoo. It took me so long to edit out all the unnecessary external sounds, but I think it was worth it. From time to time, as the sound progresses, you can hear the singing of a big parrot that was in the cage next to the little parrots I was recording. That other parrot is quite big and I think they call him 'Patagonian Parrot' (Latin name: Cyanoliseus Patagonus) Here you go, enjoy! Recorded with Zoom H4n. Please rate, comment and share. In case you download some of my sounds and use them in your audiovisual artwork, the only thing I ask from you is to let me know where and how they ended up. It would be a pleasure. Please feel free to send me a private message if you have any questions or suggestions. I really try to keep an open mind for everything. Thank you. Peace. Matt

29888.title: Cutlery12.wav
29888.description: Series of samples of cutlery in a Tupperware box. I rummaged about with my hand in this box in order to make noises that will be used in the rhythm section of a number of songs I’m working on. They are recorded with a Leem SR-105 dynamic microphone through an Edirol UA-25 directly on my computer. Such samples are very usable to create non-standard rhythm patterns, e.g. by looping them or by by putting them randomly in a song. These samples are the non-processed ones (even no noise reduction) in order to give you maximum freedom to manipulate the original recordings.
